stylometry: Decision theory is looking at each and every decision and the good and bad of it. Looking at the probability of each scenario and calculating the loss or gain of the company accordingly. A pay off table consist of probabilities and monetary values. The probabilities and values are multiplied together to give what the expected rate of return on your investment might be. So if there is a 50% chance that the market will be good and you spend 1000, the pay off table will have a 500 on the end of it. Once this step is accomplished with each scenario or value then we are able to add them up and get our expected monetary value, wich is the general amount we expect to gain.
